HEADWORD: Unpolicied
<hw>Un*pol"i*cied</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
having civil polity, or a regular form of government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Impolitic; imprudent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unpolish</ent>⟦br⟧
